*******************************************************************************
Component:	DaytonaHW
Type:		RISC OS relocatable module written in C and assembler
Purpose:	Control and interface to bits of hardware specific to Daytona
                and provide a general dumping ground for Daytona stuff that
                needs to be in a relocatable module.
Owner:		Ben Laughton
Project(s):	Daytona.
*******************************************************************************

===============================================================================
Version:	0.29.1.5.2.4
Date:		1998-05-12
Name:		Ben Laughton
CVS tag:	DaytonaHW-0_29-1_5_2_4

Fixes to on/off hook detection and dialtone generation so that it should
now be impossible to 'lose' the dialtone in any situation.

===============================================================================
Version:	0.29.1.5.2.3
Date:		1998-03-27
Name:		Richard Warren
CVS tag:	DaytonaHW-0_29-1_5_2_3

!MkMemC		added
MakeFile	MemCheckCC & LD added
module.c	MemCheck support added: #include "MemCheck:MemCheck.h", setup
		in initialise and clean up in finalise.  All compile time
		dependant on MemCheck_MEMCHECK being defined so that source
		will build without requiring MemCheck.h
		Needs sys. var. MemCheckOut$Dir set to dir. to write file to.

===============================================================================
Version:	0.29.1.5.2.2
Date:		1998-03-26
Name:		Ben Laughton
CVS tag:	DaytonaHW-0_29-1_5_2_2

Call to control LEDs now returns previous state (as described in the
specification) to enable the test software to function correctly.

===============================================================================
